Now let me summarize the new structure and provide the Nginx config. Here's the complete picture:

## Summary of Changes

**New structure in your repo:**
```
BizBio.UI/
├── public/
│   ├── profile-assets/           # Shared JS + templates (served by Nuxt)
│   │   ├── bizbio-engine.js
│   │   ├── vcard-generator.js
│   │   ├── links-helper.js
│   │   ├── wallet-integration.js
│   │   ├── vcard-downloader.js
│   │   └── templates/            # Template HTML files
│   └── fonts/                    # Shared fonts
├── profiles/                     # Keep for reference/development (NOT deployed)
```

**On VPS after deployment:**
```
/var/www/snaptap/ui/
├── current/public/
│   ├── profile-assets/           # JS + templates (served by Nuxt at /profile-assets/*)
│   └── fonts/                    # Fonts (served by Nuxt at /fonts/*)
├── profiles/                     # Persistent user profiles (served by Nginx)
│   ├── checkeredblock/
│   │   └── index.html           # References /profile-assets/bizbio-engine.js
│   └── ...
```

## Updated Nginx Config

Update `/etc/nginx/sites-available/snaptap.co.za`:

```nginx
server {
    server_name snaptap.co.za www.snaptap.co.za;

    listen 443 ssl;
    ssl_certificate /etc/letsencrypt/live/snaptap.co.za/fullchain.pem;
    ssl_certificate_key /etc/letsencrypt/live/snaptap.co.za/privkey.pem;
    include /etc/letsencrypt/options-ssl-nginx.conf;
    ssl_dhparam /etc/letsencrypt/ssl-dhparams.pem;

    # Nuxt static assets
    location ^~ /_nuxt/ {
        proxy_pass http://127.0.0.1:3001;
        proxy_set_header Host $host;
        proxy_set_header X-Real-IP $remote_addr;
        proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-For $proxy_add_x_forwarded_for;
        proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-Proto $scheme;
    }

    # Profile assets (JS, templates, fonts) — proxy to Nuxt
    location ^~ /profile-assets/ {
        proxy_pass http://127.0.0.1:3001;
        proxy_set_header Host $host;
        proxy_set_header X-Real-IP $remote_addr;
        proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-For $proxy_add_x_forwarded_for;
        proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-Proto $scheme;
    }

    # Fonts — proxy to Nuxt
    location ^~ /fonts/ {
        proxy_pass http://127.0.0.1:3001;
        proxy_set_header Host $host;
        proxy_set_header X-Real-IP $remote_addr;
        proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-For $proxy_add_x_forwarded_for;
        proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-Proto $scheme;
    }

    # Static assets (images, icons, etc.) — proxy to Nuxt
    location ~* \.(svg|png|jpg|jpeg|gif|ico|webp|avif|woff|woff2|ttf|eot|css|js|json|webmanifest)$ {
        proxy_pass http://127.0.0.1:3001;
        proxy_set_header Host $host;
        proxy_set_header X-Real-IP $remote_addr;
        proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-For $proxy_add_x_forwarded_for;
        proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-Proto $scheme;
    }

    # Known frontend routes — send to Nuxt
    location ~ ^/(login|register|dashboard|profile|settings|admin|logout|about|contact|pricing|features|organizations|catalogs|search|help|verify-email|verify-sent)(/.*)?$ {
        proxy_pass http://127.0.0.1:3001;
        proxy_http_version 1.1;
        proxy_set_header Upgrade $http_upgrade;
        proxy_set_header Connection 'upgrade';
        proxy_set_header Host $host;
        proxy_set_header X-Real-IP $remote_addr;
        proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-For $proxy_add_x_forwarded_for;
        proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-Proto $scheme;
        proxy_cache_bypass $http_upgrade;
    }

    # API routes — send to ASP.NET backend
    location ^~ /api/ {
        proxy_pass http://127.0.0.1:5000;
        proxy_set_header Host $host;
        proxy_set_header X-Real-IP $remote_addr;
        proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-For $proxy_add_x_forwarded_for;
        proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-Proto $scheme;
    }

    # Root — send to Nuxt home page
    location = / {
        proxy_pass http://127.0.0.1:3001;
        proxy_http_version 1.1;
        proxy_set_header Upgrade $http_upgrade;
        proxy_set_header Connection 'upgrade';
        proxy_set_header Host $host;
        proxy_set_header X-Real-IP $remote_addr;
        proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-For $proxy_add_x_forwarded_for;
        proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-Proto $scheme;
        proxy_cache_bypass $http_upgrade;
    }

    # Everything else is a slug — serve profile HTML from persistent directory
    location / {
        root /var/www/snaptap/ui/profiles/;
        try_files /$uri/index.html /$uri.html @api_slug_fallback;
    }

    # If no static profile file found, let ASP.NET API handle it
    location @api_slug_fallback {
        proxy_pass http://127.0.0.1:5000;
        proxy_set_header Host $host;
        proxy_set_header X-Real-IP $remote_addr;
        proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-For $proxy_add_x_forwarded_for;
        proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-Proto $scheme;
    }
}
```

## One-time setup on VPS

After deploying the new build:

```bash
# Create persistent profiles directory
mkdir -p /var/www/snaptap/ui/profiles

# Copy existing profiles from the old location (if they exist in the build)
# Or copy from your development machine
cp -r /var/www/snaptap/ui/current/public/profiles/* /var/www/snaptap/ui/profiles/ 2>/dev/null || echo "Copy profiles manually"

# Reload Nginx
sudo nginx -t && sudo systemctl reload nginx

# Reload PM2
pm2 reload ecosystem.config.cjs --env production
```

The key concept: **Profile HTML files are user content** stored persistently in `/var/www/snaptap/ui/profiles/`, while **JS/templates** are build artifacts served by Nuxt from `/profile-assets/`.

